+---
+
+> **This is a fork of [`tursodatabase/agentfs`](https://github.com/tursodatabase/agentfs).** See [Fork Changes](#fork-changes) below for what was modified and why.
+
+---
+
+## Fork Changes
+
+This fork replaces the proprietary `turso` crate with the open-source `libsql` crate and adds support for pure remote database connections. It was created for the [AiryFS](https://github.com/tysont/airyfs) project, which runs the AgentFS FUSE daemon inside a Cloudflare Container against a database hosted in a Durable Object — requiring network-only database access with no local file.
+
+### Changes from upstream
+
+**1. `turso` replaced with `libsql` (SDK + CLI, 21 files)**
+
+The upstream `turso` crate is Turso's proprietary SDK. It only supports local SQLite files (`Builder::new_local`) and embedded replicas that sync with Turso Cloud (`sync::Builder::new_remote`). The open-source `libsql` crate has a nearly identical API but adds `Builder::new_remote(url, token)` — a pure network connection where every query goes over HTTP via the Hrana protocol. No local file is created.
+
+Mechanical adaptations:
+- `prepare_cached()` → `prepare()` (libsql has no statement cache)
+- `Row::get_value(usize)` → `get_value(i32)` (index type difference)
+- ~30 sites where `Rows` must be dropped before the next connection operation (libsql holds a reference to the SQLite statement; turso copied row data)
+- Turso sync functionality removed (pull/push/checkpoint) — no libsql equivalent, not needed for remote-only use
+
+**2. Remote database support (SDK + CLI, 5 files)**
+
+- `ConnectionPool::new_remote(url, auth_token)` — creates a pool backed by `libsql::Builder::new_remote()`
+- `AgentFSOptions::with_remote(url)` + `.with_auth_token(token)` — constructor for remote mode
+- `AgentFS::open()` — detects `remote_url` and creates the pool via `new_remote()`, skipping local path resolution
+- CLI: `agentfs mount --remote-url <URL> [--auth-token <TOKEN>] <name> <mountpoint>`
+
+**3. PRAGMA fix (SDK, 1 file)**
+
+`execute_batch("PRAGMA synchronous = OFF")` fails because libsql's SQL parser classifies PRAGMAs with values as unsupported statements when sent through the batch code path. Changed to `execute()` which bypasses the parser and sends the SQL directly. Also removed `BEGIN`/`COMMIT` from the `fsync()` batch since transaction control is not applicable to remote connections.
+
+### Test status
+
+100 of 101 upstream tests pass. 1 test is ignored (uses the `aegis256` cipher which is turso-specific and not available in libsql).
+
+### Usage
+
+```bash
+# Mount against a remote Hrana-compatible server
+agentfs mount --remote-url http://localhost:8080 --auth-token "" volume /mnt/volume
+
+# All existing local functionality is unchanged
+agentfs mount myagent /mnt/volume
+```
 
